00:22:18,559 --> 00:22:23,224
however they do bring a sense of humanity to the space, and a place of refuge when channels are more chatty.

444
00:22:24,358 --> 00:22:28,743
And you may find other ways to foster a kinder space in your places.

445
00:22:28,743 --> 00:22:31,686
This is by no means the only way to create home-like feelings.

446
00:22:31,686 --> 00:22:33,407
Maybe you'll have a fun theme to your Discord.

447
00:22:33,407 --> 00:22:36,510
Maybe you'll have a metagame that people can participate in.

448
00:22:36,510 --> 00:22:39,093
Maybe you'll literally make it all about being wholesome.

449
00:22:39,627 --> 00:22:43,570
whatever you want. As you solidify your community pillars and uphold your

450
00:22:43,570 --> 00:22:46,751
community to standards you set, the better their reputation becomes.

451
00:22:46,751 --> 00:22:49,893
We've had people join KidVox purely because people had heard it was a

452
00:22:49,893 --> 00:22:52,695
positive place to be in, and most newcomers see how people

453
00:22:52,695 --> 00:22:55,937
interact, see their reputation, and naturally go along with this. It's a

454
00:22:55,937 --> 00:22:58,258
very beneficial and pleasant circle of events.

455
00:22:59,597 --> 00:23:02,240
So designing calendar communities and moderation

456
00:23:02,240 --> 00:23:03,642
is not just about risk management.

457
00:23:03,642 --> 00:23:06,105
It's lifetime value will reward you.

458
00:23:06,105 --> 00:23:07,426
People will want to interact

459
00:23:07,426 --> 00:23:09,649
and will stick around for your future games to come.

460
00:23:09,649 --> 00:23:11,371
And long-term, there's less work on your end.

461
00:23:12,259 --> 00:23:15,462
Of course, at its very core, regardless of the spaces we create,

462
00:23:15,462 --> 00:23:19,686
Kitfox and any other studio exist to sell products, games, t-shirts, limited box sets,

463
00:23:19,686 --> 00:23:23,810
whatever. But while we're at it, we might as well do our best to make

464
00:23:23,810 --> 00:23:28,354
the places we touch a little bit more positive. The user experience in games is important,

465
00:23:28,354 --> 00:23:33,039
but combined with a warm, friendly user experience in the community, that's good design.

